-- Colruyt, Iberdrola, Portugal Telecom, RWE, Swatch: European Equity Preview
-- Whitney Kisling
-- 2010-06-29T04:00:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/colruyt-iberdrola-portugal-telecom-rwe-swatch-european-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  climbed 1.2 percent to 251.36.
The  Stoxx 50 Index  advanced 1.3 percent to 2,431.08. The  Euro
Stoxx 50 Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, rallied
1.5 percent to 2,668.67.  
 Cie. de Saint-Gobain SA  (SGO FP): Europe’s biggest supplier
of building materials agreed to sell its advanced ceramics
business to CoorsTek Inc. for $245 million. The shares added 2.5
percent to 32.70 euros.  
 Colruyt NV  (COLR BB): Belgium’s biggest discount food
retailer said fiscal full-year net income rose 8.3 percent to
329.6 million euros ($404.5 million) and raised its dividend by
11 percent. Analysts had estimated profit of 329.3 million
euros, the average of 13  estimates  compiled by Bloomberg.
Colruyt increased 0.8 percent to 194.10 euros.  
 Ferrovial SA  (FER SM): The owner of Heathrow airport near
London holds its annual shareholders’ meeting. The shares rose
3.3 percent to 5.62 euros.  
 Iberdrola SA  (IBE SM): Spain’s biggest power company was
downgraded to “hold” from “buy” at Independent Research GmbH
by equity analyst  Sven Diermeier . The 6-month share price
estimate is 5.50 euros. The shares rose 0.2 percent to 4.95
euros.  
 Portugal Telecom SGPS SA  (PTC PL): Chief Executive Officer
Zeinal Bava of Portugal’s biggest phone company is scheduled to
speak at a conference in Lisbon tomorrow, a day before
shareholders meet to discuss Telefonica SA’s offer to buy the
company’s stake in the joint-venture that controls Vivo
Participacoes SA. The shares lost 2.3 percent to 8.35 euros.  
 RWE AG  (RWE GY): RWE Npower Plc, the U.K. unit of Germany’s
second-biggest utility, applied to install a mast in the Bristol
Channel that will survey wind speeds, waves and tidal conditions
for its Atlantic Array offshore wind farm. RWE shares slipped
0.1 percent to 55.08 euros.  
 Swatch Group AG  (UHR VX): Nicolas Hayek, chairman of the
maker of Omega and Breguet timepieces, died of heart failure,
the company said. The shares rose 2.6 percent to 325.4 Swiss
francs.  
 Technip SA  (TEC FP): Europe’s second-largest oilfield-
services provider will pay $338 million to settle U.S. claims it
paid bribes to Nigerian government officials to win more than $6
billion in construction contracts, the Justice Department said.
The stock rose 2.1 percent to 50.58 euros.  
